# Project Setup — mise

Use **mise** (`mise.toml`) to pin all tool versions at the repo root. Ensures every developer and CI job uses exactly the same versions. Works for any language — not just Python.

## mise.toml (commit to git)

```toml
[tools]
python = "3.12"
node = "20.11"
just = "1.36"
# add other tools as needed: go, rust, terraform, etc.
```

## Bootstrap

```bash
# Install mise (once per machine)
curl https://mise.run | sh

# Install all pinned tool versions for the project
mise install

# Verify active versions
mise current
```

CI must call `mise install` as the first step before any build or test command:

```yaml
# GitHub Actions example
- name: Install tool versions
  run: mise install
```

## Add to justfile

```justfile
# Install all tool versions pinned in mise.toml
bootstrap:
    mise install
    uv sync
```

## Rules

- `mise.toml` lives at the repo root and is always committed to git.
- Pin at least major + minor: `python = "3.12"` not `"3"`.
- Do not use `.tool-versions` (asdf format) alongside `mise.toml` — pick one.
- If a tool is in `mise.toml`, never install it globally with Homebrew or manually — let mise manage it.
